n33:   - Test JSON serialization/deserialization for all types\n34:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/common/types/... -v`\n35: \n36: - [ ] **T1.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` file\n37:   - Define constants:\n38:     - `DefaultSandboxTTL = 8 * time.Hour`\n39:     - `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout = 15 * time.Minute`\n40:     - `DefaultMaxSessionDuration = 8 * time.Hour`\n41:     - `DefaultSessionTimeout = 15 * time.Minute`\n42:     - `SandboxCreationTimeout = 2 * time.Minute`\n43:     - `SandboxDeleteTimeout = 30 * time.Second`\n44:   - Define label/annotation key constants:\n45:     - `LabelKeySessionID = \"runtime.agentcube.io/session-id\"`\n46:     - `LabelKeyWorkloadName = \"runtime.agentcube.io/workload-name\"`\n47:     - `LabelKeySandboxName = \"runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name\"`\n48:     - `LabelKeyManagedBy = \"managed-by\"`\n49:     - `AnnotationKeyIdleTimeout = \"runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout\"`\n50:     - `AnnotationKeyPodName = \"agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name\"`\n51:   - Define GVR constants:\n52:     - `SandboxGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{Group: \"agents.x-k8s.io\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"sandboxes\"}`\n53:     - `SandboxClaimGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{Group: \"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"sandboxclaims\"}`\n54:   - Define kind constants:\n55:     - `SandboxKind = \"Sandbox\"`\n56:     - `SandboxClaimKind = \"SandboxClaim\"`\n57:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n58: \n59: - [ ] **T1.4** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults_test.go` file\n60:   - Test all constant values match design specification\n61:   - Test GVR constants are correctly formed\n62:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestDefaults -v`\n63: \n64: ### Phase 2: K8s Client Infrastructure\n65: \n66: - [ ] **T2.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/k8s_client.go` file\n67:   - Define `K8sClient` struct with fields:\n68:     - `dynamicClient dynamic.Interface`\n69:     - `informerFactory externalversions.SharedInformerFactory`\n70:     - `agentRuntimeLister listers.AgentRuntimeLister`\n71:     - `codeInterpreterLister listers.CodeInterpreterLister`\n72:     - `podLister corev1listers.PodLister`\n73:     - `coreClient kubernetes.Interface`\n74:   - Define `ClientCache` struct for per-user client caching (if auth enabled)\n75:   - Implement `NewK8sClient(config *rest.Config) (*K8sClient, error)` function\n76:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n77: \n78: - [ ] **T2.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/k8s_client_test.go` file\n79:   - Test `K8sClient` initialization with fake clientset\n80:   - Test informer factory creation\n81:   - Test lister access methods\n82:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestK8sClient -v`\n83: \n84: - [ ] **T2.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/informers.go` file\n85:   - Define `Informers` struct wrapping `SharedInformerFactory`\n86:   - Implement `NewInformers(k8sClient *K8sClient) *Informers` function\n87:   - Implement `Start(ctx context.Context)` method\n88:   - Implement `WaitForCacheSync(ctx context.Context) bool` method\n89:   - Implement `GetAgentRuntimeInformer() runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeInformer` method\n90:   - Implement `GetCodeInterpreterInformer() runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterInformer` method\n91:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n92: \n93: - [ ] **T2.4** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/informers_test.go` file\n94:   - Test informer start and stop\n95:   - Test cache sync with timeout\n96:   - Test lister retrieval\n97:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestInformers -v`\n98: \n99: ### Phase 3: Store Integration\n100: \n101: - [ ] **T3.1** Define Store interface in `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go`\n102:   - Add `Store` interface with methods:\n103:     - `StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error`\n104:     - `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n105:     - `UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error`\n106:     - `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error`\n107:     - `ListSandboxes(ctx context.Context) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n108:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n109: \n110: - [ ] **T3.2** Create Store implementation stub (interface only for now)\n111:   - Note: Actual Redis Store implementation is in AR-006 or separate module\n112:   - Create mock Store for testing purposes\n113:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n114: \n115: ### Phase 4: Sandbox Controller & Watcher\n116: \n117: - [ ] **T4.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_controller.go` file\n118:   - Define `SandboxReconciler` struct with fields:\n119:     - `k8sClient *K8sClient`\n120:     - `watchers map[string]chan struct{}`\n121:     - `mutex sync.RWMutex`\n122:   - Implement `WatchSandboxOnce(namespace, name string) (<-chan struct{}, error)` method:\n123:     - Register watcher before CR creation\n124:     - Return channel that closes when sandbox enters \"running\" state\n125:   - Implement `notifyWatcher(namespace, name string)` private method\n126:   - Implement `getSandboxStatus(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string) (string, error)` method\n127:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n128: \n129: - [ ] **T4.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_controller_test.go` file\n130:   - Test `WatchSandboxOnce` registration\n131:   - Test watcher channel closes on running status\n132:   - Test concurrent watchers\n133:   - Test watcher cleanup\n134:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestSandboxController -v`\n135: \n136: ### Phase 5: Workload Builder\n137: \n138: - [ ] **T5.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go` file\n139:   - Implement `buildSandboxObject(runtime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, sessionID string) (*unstructured.Unstructured, error)`:\n140:     - Generate sandbox name: `{workloadName}-{RandString(8)}`\n141:     - Set APIVersion: `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`\n142:     - Set Kind: `Sandbox`\n143:     - Set labels: session-id, workload-name, sandbox-name, managed-by\n144:     - Set annotations: idle-timeout\n145:     - Set spec.podTemplate from runtime.Spec.Template\n146:     - Set spec.replicas = 1\n147:     - Set spec.lifecycle.shutdownTime = now + MaxSessionDuration\n148:   - Implement `RandString(n int) string` helper for 8-char lowercase random string\n149:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n150: \n151: - [ ] **T5.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder_test.go` file\n152:   - Test `buildSandboxObject` with valid AgentRuntime:\n153:     - Verify name format (workload-8char)\n154:     - Verify labels and annotations\n155:     - Verify podTemplate copied correctly\n156:     - Verify replicas = 1\n157:   - Test `RandString` generates 8 lowercase letters\n158:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestBuildSandboxObject -v`\n159: \n160: - [ ] **T5.3** Implement `buildSandboxClaimObject(ci *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, sessionID string) (*unstructured.Unstructured, error)`:\n161:   - Set APIVersion: `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`\n162:   - Set Kind: `SandboxClaim`\n163:   - Minimal metadata (labels and annotations)\n164:   - No full PodSpec\n165:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n166: \n167: - [ ] **T5.4** Create test for `buildSandboxClaimObject`:\n168:   - Verify correct GVK\n169:   - Verify minimal metadata\n170:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestBuildSandboxClaimObject -v`\n171: \n172: - [ ] **T5.5** Implement `buildCodeInterpreterSandboxObject(ci *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, sessionID string, publicKey []byte) (*unstructured.Unstructured, error)`:\n173:   - Build full Sandbox for WarmPoolSize == 0\n174:   - Single container named \"code-interpreter\"\n175:   - Inject `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` env var if AuthMode=picod and publicKey available\n176:   - Set default ports if spec.Ports empty: `[{Port: 8080, Protocol: HTTP, PathPrefix: \"/\"}]`\n177:   - Apply optional fields: Command, Args, Environment, Resources, RuntimeClassName, ImagePullPolicy, ImagePullSecrets\n178:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n179: \n180: - [ ] **T5.6** Create test for `buildCodeInterpreterSandboxObject`:\n181:   - Test with AuthMode=picod: verify public key injected\n182:   - Test with AuthMode=none: verify no public key\n183:   - Test with empty Ports: verify default 8080\n184:   - Test with custom Ports: verify copied correctly\n185:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestBuildCodeInterpreterSandbox -v`\n186: \n187: ### Phase 6: Sandbox Creator - Core Creation Flow\n188: \n189: - [ ] **T6.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_creator.go` file\n190:   - Define `sandboxCreator` struct with fields:\n191:     - `k8sClient *K8sClient`\n192:     - `sandboxController *SandboxReconciler`\n193:     - `storeClient Store`\n194:     - `publicKey []byte`\n195:   - Implement `newSandboxCreator(...)` constructor\n196:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n197: \n198: - [ ] **T6.2** Implement `createSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *unstructured.Unstructured, isWarmPool bool, userClient dynamic.Interface) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`:\n199:   - Phase 1: Register watcher (WatchSandboxOnce)\n200:   - Phase 2: Store placeholder SandboxInfo (status=pending)\n201:   - Phase 3: Create CR via dynamic client\n202:   - Phase 4: Wait for running (2-minute timeout)\n203:   - Phase 5: Resolve Pod IP and entryPoints\n204:   - Phase 6: Update Store with full SandboxInfo (status=running)\n205:   - Implement rollback on each phase failure\n206:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n207: \n208: - [ ] **T6.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_creator_test.go` file\n209:   - Test successful creation flow:\n210:     - Mock watcher channel (close immediately)\n211:     - Mock dynamic client Create\n212:     - Mock Store operations\n213:     - Verify correct SandboxInfo returned\n214:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestCreateSandbox_Success -v`\n215: \n216: - [ ] **T6.4** Test creation timeout:\n217:   - Mock watcher channel that never closes\n218:   - Use 2-minute timeout context\n219:   - Verify CR deleted after timeout\n220:   - Verify Store record deleted\n221:   - Verify error returned\n222:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestCreateSandbox_Timeout -v`\n223: \n224: - [ ] **T6.5** Test rollback on creation failure:\n225:   - Mock dynamic client Create failure\n226:   - Verify Store placeholder deleted\n227:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestCreateSandbox_Rollback -v`\n228: \n229: - [ ] **T6.6** Test rollback on IP resolution failure:\n230:   - Mock successful CR creation\n231:   - Mock resolvePodIP failure\n232:   - Verify CR deleted\n233:   - Verify Store record deleted\n234:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestCreateSandbox_IPResolutionFailure -v`\n235: \n236: ### Phase 7: Pod IP Resolution & EntryPoint Building\n237: \n238: - [ ] **T7.1** Implement `resolvePodIP(ctx context.Context, sandboxNamespace, sandboxName string) (string, error)` in `sandbox_creator.go`:\n239:   - Priority 1: Use sandbox name as pod name\n240:   - Priority 2: Check sandbox annotation `agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name`\n241:   - Priority 3: Get pod from podLister, verify Phase=Running and PodIP non-empty\n242:   - Priority 4: Fallback: list pods by label `SandboxNameLabelKey`, match owner reference\n243:   - Return error if no running pod found\n244:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n245: \n246: - [ ] **T7.2** Create tests for `resolvePodIP`:\n247:   - Test with pod name matching sandbox name\n248:   - Test with annotation override\n249:   - Test with pod not running (Phase != Running)\n250:   - Test with owner reference matching\n251:   - Test with no pod found\n252:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestResolvePodIP -v`\n253: \n254: - [ ] **T7.3** Implement `resolveEntryPoints(ctx context.Context, namespace, sandboxName string, ports []runtimev1alpha1.TargetPort) ([]types.SandboxEntryPoint, error)`:\n255:   - Call resolvePodIP to get pod IP\n256:   - Call buildEntryPoints with pod IP and ports\n257:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n258: \n259: - [ ] **T7.4** Implement `buildEntryPoints(podIP string, ports []runtimev1alpha1.TargetPort) []types.SandboxEntryPoint`:\n260:   - Iterate over ports\n261:   - Build SandboxEntryPoint: `{Path: p.PathPrefix, Protocol: string(p.Protocol), Endpoint: fmt.Sprintf(\"%s:%d\", podIP, p.Port)}`\n262:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n263: \n264: - [ ] **T7.5** Create tests for `buildEntryPoints`:\n265:   - Test with multiple ports\n266:   - Test with HTTP and HTTPS protocols\n267:   - Test endpoint format: `ip:port`\n268:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestBuildEntryPoints -v`\n269: \n270: ### Phase 8: HTTP Handlers\n271: \n272: - [ ] **T8.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_handler.go` file\n273:   - Define `SandboxHandler` struct with fields:\n274:     - `creator *sandboxCreator`\n275:     - `k8sClient *K8sClient`\n276:     - `logger Logger`\n277:   - Implement `Register(r chi.Router)` method:\n278:     - POST /v1/agent-runtime\n279:     - POST /v1/code-interpreter\n280:     - DELETE /v1/sessions/:sessionId (optional, for cleanup)\n281:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/...`\n282: \n283: - [ ] **T8.2** Implement `handleAgentRuntimeCreate(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request)`:\n284:   - Parse JSON request body into `CreateSandboxRequest`\n285:   - Override Kind = \"AgentRuntime\"\n286:   - Validate request (call Validate() method)\n287:   - Get AgentRuntime from informer lister\n288:   - Check if runtime.Spec.Template != nil (return 400 if nil)\n289:   - Generate sessionID (UUID)\n290:   - Call buildSandboxObject\n291:   - Call createSandbox\n292:   - Build CreateSandboxResponse\n293:   - Return 200 with JSON response\n294:   - Handle errors: 400 (validation), 404 (not found), 500 (internal)\n295:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/...`\n296: \n297: - [ ] **T8.3** Implement `handleCodeInterpreterCreate(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request)`:\n298:   - Parse JSON request body\n299:   - Override Kind = \"CodeInterpreter\"\n300:   - Validate request\n301:   - Get CodeInterpreter from informer lister\n302:   - Check WarmPoolSize:\n303:     - If > 0: buildSandboxClaimObject, createSandbox with isWarmPool=true\n304:     - If == 0: buildCodeInterpreterSandboxObject, createSandbox\n305:   - Inject public key if AuthMode=picod\n306:   - Apply default ports if Ports empty\n307:   - Return CreateSandboxResponse\n308:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/...`\n309: \n310: - [ ] **T8.4** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_handler_test.go` file\n311:   - Test WM-001: `TestHandleAgentRuntimeCreate_Success`:\n312:     - Mock AgentRuntime in fake informer\n313:     - Mock createSandbox success\n314:     - Verify 200 response with sessionId and entryPoints\n315:   - Test WM-002: `TestHandleAgentRuntimeCreate_Idempotent`:\n316:     - Mock Store with existing sessionID\n317:     - Verify same sessionId returned\n318:   - Test WM-003: `TestHandleAgentRuntimeCreate_MissingPodTemplate`:\n319:     - Mock AgentRuntime with Template=nil\n320:     - Verify 400 response with \"pod template\" message\n321:   - Test invalid request body (JSON parse error)\n322:   - Test validation errors (empty name/namespace)\n323:   - Test not found error (Informer returns IsNotFound)\n324:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/... -run TestHandleAgentRuntimeCreate -v`\n325: \n326: - [ ] **T8.5** Create tests for CodeInterpreter handler:\n327:   - Test WarmPool path (WarmPoolSize > 0)\n328:   - Test default ports (Ports empty)\n329:   - Test AuthMode=picod with public key injection\n330:   - Test AuthMode=none without public key\n331:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/... -run TestHandleCodeInterpreterCreate -v`\n332: \n333: ### Phase 9: Error Handling & Response Formatting\n334: \n335: - [ ] **T9.1** Implement error mapping in handlers:\n336:   - JSON bind error → 400: `{\"message\":\"Invalid request body\"}`\n337:   - Validation error → 400: `{\"message\":\"<field> is required\"}`\n338:   - Template missing → 400: `{\"message\":\"agent runtime not found: ... pod template missing\"}`\n339:   - Not found → 404: `{\"message\":\"agent runtime not found\"}`\n340:   - Timeout → 500: `{\"message\":\"internal server error\"}`\n341:   - K8s API error → 500: `{\"message\":\"internal server error\"}`\n342:   - Store error → 500: `{\"message\":\"internal server error\"}`\n343:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/...`\n344: \n345: - [ ] **T9.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/response.go` file:\n346:   - Implement `writeJSONResponse(w http.ResponseWriter, status int, data interface{})` helper\n347:   - Implement `writeErrorResponse(w http.ResponseWriter, status int, message string)` helper\n348:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/...`\n349: \n350: - [ ] **T9.3** Create tests for error response formatting:\n351:   - Test each error type produces correct status and JSON\n352:   - Verify Content-Type: application/json header\n353:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/... -run TestErrorResponse -v`\n354: \n355: ### Phase 10: Authentication Middleware\n356: \n357: - [ ] **T10.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/auth.go` file\n358:   - Define context keys:\n359:     - `contextKeyUserToken`\n360:     - `contextKeyServiceAccount`\n361:     - `contextKeyServiceAccountName`\n362:     - `contextKeyNamespace`\n363:   - Implement `authMiddleware(publicKey []byte, enableAuth bool) func(http.Handler) http.Handler`:\n364:     - If EnableAuth=false: pass through\n365:     - If EnableAuth=true:\n366:       - Extract Bearer token from Authorization header\n367:       - Validate token via Kubernetes TokenReview API\n368:       - Extract ServiceAccount name and namespace\n369:       - Store token and SA info in context\n370:       - Return 401 if missing/invalid token\n371:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/...`\n372: \n373: - [ ] **T10.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/auth_test.go` file\n374:   - Test with EnableAuth=false: no validation\n375:   - Test with valid Bearer token: context populated\n376:   - Test with missing Authorization header: 401\n377:   - Test with invalid token: 401\n378:   - Test TokenReview API call\n379:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/... -run TestAuthMiddleware -v`\n380: \n381: - [ ] **T10.3** Implement per-user client creation (if auth enabled):\n382:   - Modify `sandboxCreator` to accept userClient from context\n383:   - Implement `GetOrCreateUserK8sClient(token string, namespace string) (dynamic.Interface, error)` in k8s_client.go\n384:   - Cache clients by token+namespace\n385:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n386: \n387: ### Phase 11: Server Integration\n388: \n389: - [ ] **T11.1** Update `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go`:\n390:   - Add fields to `HTTPServer` struct:\n391:     - `k8sClient *K8sClient`\n392:     - `informers *Informers`\n393:     - `sandboxController *SandboxReconciler`\n394:     - `storeClient Store`\n395:     - `publicKey []byte`\n396:     - `enableAuth bool`\n397:   - Implement `NewHTTPServerWithWorkloadManager(cfg Config, k8sClient *K8sClient, storeClient Store, publicKey []byte, enableAuth bool, logger Logger) (*HTTPServer, error)`\n398:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n399: \n400: - [ ] **T11.2** Implement server initialization sequence:\n401:   - Initialize Informers\n402:   - Start informers and wait for cache sync (timeout 1 minute)\n403:   - Initialize SandboxReconciler\n404:   - Initialize sandboxCreator\n405:   - Initialize SandboxHandler\n406:   - Register middleware: Recovery → Logging → CORS → Auth → SandboxHandler\n407:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n408: \n409: - [ ] **T11.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/server_test.go` integration test:\n410:   - Test server startup with fake clients\n411:   - Test informer sync\n412:   - Test handler registration\n413:   - Test full request flow: POST /v1/agent-runtime → response\n414:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestServerIntegration -v`\n415: \n416: ### Phase 12: Garbage Collector\n417: \n418: - [ ] **T12.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go` file\n419:   - Define `garbageCollector` struct with fields:\n420:     - `k8sClient *K8sClient`\n421:     - `storeClient Store`\n422:     - `interval time.Duration`\n423:     - `logger Logger`\n424:   - Implement `newGarbageCollector(...)` constructor\n425:   - Implement `Start(ctx context.Context)` method with periodic tick loop\n426:   - Implement `gcLoop(ctx context.Context)` method:\n427:     - List all sandboxes from Store\n428:     - Check expiresAt < now: delete CR + delete Store record\n429:     - Check lastActivity > idleTimeout: delete CR + delete Store record\n430:     - Check createdAt + MaxSessionDuration < now: delete CR + delete Store record\n431:   - Implement `deleteSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxInfo *types.SandboxInfo)` helper\n432:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n433: \n434: - [ ] **T12.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go` file\n435:   - Test expired sandbox cleanup\n436:   - Test idle timeout cleanup\n437:   - Test max session duration cleanup\n438:   - Test deletion success (CR + Store)\n439:   - Test deletion failure handling\n440:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestGarbageCollector -v`\n441: \n442: - [ ] **T12.3** Integrate GC into server:\n443:   - Add `garbageCollector` to HTTPServer\n444:   - Start GC in `Start()` method\n445:   - Stop GC in `Stop()` method\n446:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n447: \n448: ### Phase 13: Integration Tests\n449: \n450: - [ ] **T13.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go` file\n451:   - Define `testEnv` struct with all dependencies\n452:   - Implement `newTestEnv(t *testing.T) *testEnv`:\n453:     - Start miniredis\n454:     - Create fake clientset with AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter\n455:     - Create fake dynamic client\n456:     - Initialize all components\n457:     - Build HTTPServer\n458:   - Implement `cleanupTestEnv(t *testing.T, env *testEnv)`\n459:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n460: \n461: - [ ] **T13.2** Implement integration test: Create AgentRuntime Sandbox:\n462:   - Setup testEnv with valid AgentRuntime in cache\n463:   - Send POST /v1/agent-runtime request\n464:   - Verify 200 response\n465:   - Verify sessionId in response\n466:   - Verify entryPoints in response\n467:   - Verify Store has SandboxInfo record\n468:   - Verify CR created in dynamic client\n469:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestIntegrationCreateAgentRuntime -v`\n470: \n471: - [ ] **T13.3** Implement integration test: Create CodeInterpreter Sandbox:\n472:   - Setup with CodeInterpreter (WarmPoolSize=0)\n473:   - Send POST /v1/code-interpreter\n474:   - Verify 200 response\n475:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestIntegrationCreateCodeInterpreter -v`\n476: \n477: - [ ] **T13.4** Implement integration test: Create SandboxClaim:\n478:   - Setup with CodeInterpreter (WarmPoolSize=3)\n479:   - Send POST /v1/code-interpreter\n480:   - Verify SandboxClaim created (not full Sandbox)\n481:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestIntegrationCreateSandboxClaim -v`\n482: \n483: ### Phase 14: Validation & Quality Gates\n484: \n485: - [ ] **T14.1** Run `go vet ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n486:   - Fix all issues\n487:   - Verify: zero issues\n488: \n489: - [ ] **T14.2** Run `golangci-lint run ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n490:   - Fix all linting issues\n491:   - Verify: zero issues\n492: \n493: - [ ] **T14.3** Run all unit tests:\n494:   - Command: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -v -race -coverprofile=coverage.out`\n495:   - Verify: all tests pass\n496:   - Verify: no race conditions detected\n497:   - Verify: coverage > 80% for core files\n498: \n499: - [ ] **T14.4** Verify JSON tags use camelCase in all new files:\n500:   - Check sandbox.go, sandbox_handler.go, response.go\n501:   - Verify: `grep -E 'json:\"[a-z]' pkg/workloadmanager/**/*.go`\n502: \n503: - [ ] **T14.5** Verify godoc comments:\n504:   - All exported types have comments\n505:   - All exported functions have comments\n506:   - All exported methods have comments\n507:   - Verify: `godoc -http=:6060` and browse\n508: \n509: - [ ] **T14.6** Verify error handling:\n510:   - All HTTP errors return JSON response\n511:   - All errors have appropriate status codes\n512:   - All critical errors logged\n513:   - Verify: manual code review\n514: \n515: - [ ] **T14.7** Verify rollback logic:\n516:   - Creation timeout deletes CR\n517:   - Creation failure deletes Store placeholder\n518:   - IP resolution failure deletes CR\n519:   - Store update failure logs warning\n520:   - Verify: manual code review + test coverage\n521: \n522: ### Phase 15: Documentation\n523: \n524: - [ ] **T15.1** Update `pkg/workloadmanager/doc.go`:\n525:   - Add section on Sandbox creation handlers\n526:   - Add section on Informers\n527:   - Add section on Store integration\n528:   - Add section on Authentication\n529:   - Add section on Garbage Collection\n530: \n531: - [ ] **T15.2** Add inline comments for complex logic:\n532:   - Comment watcher registration before CR creation\n533:   - Comment rollback strategy\n534:   - Comment Pod IP resolution priority\n535:   - Comment WarmPool vs full Sandbox decision\n536: \n537: - [ ] **T15.3** Verify package-level examples in godoc\n538: \n539: ---\n540: \n541: ## Task Dependencies\n542: \n543: ```\n544: T1.1 → T1.2 → T1.3 → T1.4 [Foundation: Types & Constants]\n545:    │\n546:    └→ T2.1 → T2.2 → T2.3 → T2.4 [K8s Client Infrastructure]\n547:    │\n548:    └→ T3.1 → T3.2 [Store Integration]\n549:    │\n550:    └→ T4.1 → T4.2 [Sandbox Controller & Watcher]\n551:    │\n552:    └→ T5.1 → T5.2 → T5.3 → T5.4 → T5.5 → T5.6 [Workload Builder]\n553:    │\n554:    └→ T6.1 → T6.2 → T6.3 → T6.4 → T6.5 → T6.6 [Sandbox Creator Core]\n555:    │        │\n556:    │        └→ T7.1 → T7.2 → T7.3 → T7.4 → T7.5 [Pod IP & EntryPoints]\n557:    │\n558:    └→ T8.1 → T8.2 → T8.3 → T8.4 → T8.5 [HTTP Handlers]\n559:    │        │\n560:    │        └→ T9.1 → T9.2 → T9.3 [Error Handling]\n561:    │\n562:    └→ T10.1 → T10.2 → T10.3 [Authentication Middleware]\n563:    │\n564:    └→ T11.1 → T11.2 → T11.3 [Server Integration]\n565:    │\n566:    └→ T12.1 → T12.2 → T12.3 [Garbage Collector]\n567:    │\n568:    └→ T13.1 → T13.2 → T13.3 → T13.4 [Integration Tests]\n569:    │\n570:    └→ T14.1 → T14.2 → T14.3 → T14.4 → T14.5 → T14.6 → T14.7 [Validation]\n571:    │\n572:    └→ T15.1 → T15.2 → T15.3 [Documentation]\n573: ```\n574: \n575: ---\n576: \n577: ## Verification Commands\n578: \n579: | Task | Verification Command |\n580: |------|----------------------|\n581: | T1.1 | `go build ./pkg/common/types/...` |\n582: | T1.2 | `go test ./pkg/common/types/... -v` |\n583: | T1.3 | `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` |\n584: | T2.1 | `grep -q \"type K8sClient struct\" pkg/workloadmanager/k8s_client.go` |\n585: | T4.1 | `grep -q \"WatchSandboxOnce\" pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_controller.go` |\n586: | T5.1 | `grep -q \"buildSandboxObject\" pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go` |\n587: | T6.2 | `grep -q \"func.*createSandbox\" pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_creator.go` |\n588: | T8.1 | `grep -q \"POST.*agent-runtime\" pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_handler.go` |\n589: | T10.1 | `grep -q \"authMiddleware\" pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/auth.go` |\n590: | T12.1 | `grep -q \"garbageCollector\" pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go` |\n591: | T14.1 | `go vet ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` |\n592: | T14.2 | `golangci-lint run ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` |\n593: | T14.3 | `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -v -race -coverprofile=coverage.out` |\n594: \n595: ---\n596: \n597: ## Acceptance Criteria\n598: \n599: - [ ] All types defined per design.md specification\n600: - [ ] JSON tags use camelCase for all API types\n601: - [ ] Complete godoc comments for all exported types and functions\n602: - [ ] Pass `go vet` with zero issues\n603: - [ ] Pass `golangci-lint` with zero issues\n604: - [ ] All unit tests pass with >80% coverage for core files\n605: - [ ] No race conditions detected in tests\n606: - [ ] Integration tests cover WM-001/002/003 scenarios\n607: - [ ] Error handling returns appropriate HTTP status codes and JSON responses\n608: - [ ] Rollback logic implemented for all failure scenarios\n609: - [ ] Informer cache sync with 1-minute timeout\n610: - [ ] Sandbox creation timeout (2 minutes) enforced\n611: - [ ] Authentication middleware validates tokens when EnableAuth=true\n612: - [ ] Garbage collector cleans up expired/idle/max-duration sandboxes\n613: - [ ] POST /v1/agent-runtime endpoint functional\n614: - [ ] POST /v1/code-interpreter endpoint functional with WarmPool support\n615: - [ ] Pod IP resolution handles all priority cases\n616: - [ ] EntryPoint building produces correct format\n617: \n618: ---\n619: \n620: ## Files Modified/Created\n621: \n622: | File | Status | Description |\n623: |------|--------|-------------|\n624: | `pkg/common/types/sandbox.go` | Created | Request/Response/Info types |\n625: | `pkg/common/types/sandbox_test.go` | Created | Type validation tests |\n626: | `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` | Created | Constants and defaults |\n627: | `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults_test.go` | Created | Constants tests |\n628: | `pkg/workloadmanager/k8s_client.go` | Created | K8s client wrapper |\n629: | `pkg/workloadmanager/k8s_client_test.go` | Created | Client tests |\n630: | `pkg/workloadmanager/informers.go` | Created | Informer management |\n631: | `pkg/workloadmanager/informers_test.go` | Created | Informer tests |\n632: | `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` | Updated | Add Store interface |\n633: | `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_controller.go` | Created | Reconciler & watcher |\n634: | `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_controller_test.go` | Created | Controller tests |\n635: | `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go` | Created | Sandbox object builders |\n636: | `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder_test.go` | Created | Builder tests |\n637: | `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_creator.go` | Created | Core creation flow |\n638: | `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_creator_test.go` | Created | Creator tests |\n639: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_handler.go` | Created | HTTP handlers |\n640: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_handler_test.go` | Created | Handler tests |\n641: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/response.go` | Created | Response helpers |\n642: | `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/auth.go` | Created | Auth middleware |\n643: | `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/auth_test.go` | Created | Auth tests |\n644: | `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go` | Updated | Integrate all components |\n645: | `pkg/workloadmanager/server_test.go` | Updated | Server integration tests |\n646: | `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go` | Created | GC implementation |\n647: | `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go` | Created | GC tests |\n648: | `pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go` | Created | Full integration tests |\n649: | `pkg/workloadmanager/doc.go` | Updated | Package documentation |\n650: \n651: ---\n652: \n653: ## Notes\n654: \n655: - **Dependencies**: Requires client-go generated from AR-001/002 (AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter types)\n656: - **External CRDs**: Sandbox and SandboxClaim CRDs from `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` (external, not in this project)\n657: - **Store**: Redis implementation may be in separate module (AR-006 or similar), use interface for now\n658: - **Testing Strategy**: Follow TDD manifest from `testing/agentcube_tdd_manifest.md`\n659: - **Stage ST-3**: Design complete, ready for implementation breakdown\n660: - **Reference**: `sandbox-orchestration/AR-005-sandbox-creation-processor/design.md` contains full specification\n661: - **Code Style**: Follow existing patterns in pkg/workloadmanager (chi router, Handler interface)\n662: - **TDD**: Write tests before implementation for each component\n663: - **Rollback**: Critical requirement - ensure all failure paths clean up resources\n664: - **Timeout**: 2-minute sandbox creation timeout is hard requirement from spec\n665: - **WarmPool**: CodeInterpreter WarmPoolSize > 0 creates SandboxClaim, not full Sandbox\n\n(End of file - total 665 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器 Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器 |\n| Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: Foundation - Common Types & Constants\n\n- [ ] **T1.1** Create `pkg/common/types/sandbox.go` file\n  - Define `CreateSandboxRequest` struct with fields: `Kind`, `Name`, `Namespace`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-005/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775845143125,"end":1775845143145}}}}
